# AgentGOD Agent System Conventions

## Design-First Principle

Never implement an agent before its design document exists. Follow this order:

1. Create a system design doc (use `~/.cursor/skills/agent-system-architect/templates/system-design-doc.md`)
2. Create an agent spec for each agent (use `~/.cursor/skills/agent-system-architect/templates/agent-spec.md`)
3. Review design against anti-patterns (`~/.cursor/skills/agent-system-architect/references/anti-patterns.md`)
4. Only then proceed to implementation

## Agent Naming

- Agent identifiers: lowercase, hyphens only, 3-50 characters (e.g., `code-reviewer`, `research-scout`)
- Skill directories: match agent identifier exactly
- Rule files: `<agent-name>.mdc` or `<concern-name>.mdc`
- MCP config keys: match the service name, not the agent name

## File Organization

```
AgentGOD/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/           # Project-level rules (always-apply conventions)
├── designs/             # System design documents
│   ├── system-design.md # Overall architecture
│   └── agent-specs/     # Individual agent specifications
├── agents/              # Agent implementation files
├── skills/              # Project-specific skills (if needed)
└── tests/               # Integration and end-to-end tests
```

## Agent Design Constraints

- Each agent's system prompt must be under 800 words
- Each agent may use at most 8 tools
- Each agent connects to at most 3 MCP servers
- Every destructive operation (file write, API POST/PUT/DELETE, database mutation) requires either:
  - An explicit human approval gate, OR
  - Documented justification for why autonomous execution is safe

## MCP Security

- API keys go in environment variables, never in committed files
- Use project-scope MCP config (`.mcp.json`) for project-specific servers
- Use global config (`~/.cursor/mcp.json`) only for universally needed servers
- Document which MCP servers each agent uses and why in the agent spec

## Communication Standards

- All agent-to-agent messages must include: `task_id`, `source_agent`, `timestamp`
- Define timeout and retry policy for every communication path
- Implement circuit breakers for external API dependencies
- Set max iteration limits for any evaluator-optimizer loops (default: 5)

## Quality Gates

Before declaring an agent system "ready":
- [ ] All agents have specs in `designs/agent-specs/`
- [ ] System design document exists and is current
- [ ] Anti-pattern checklist has been reviewed
- [ ] Each agent has at least 2 test cases
- [ ] End-to-end workflow tested with realistic input
- [ ] MCP token budget verified (total context consumption documented)
